---
import ArticleLayout from "../../components/ArticleLayout.astro";

const title = "Memory: How the Brain Stores You — Science";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<ArticleLayout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header>
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Atlas</a>
        <span class="chip">MIND</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Memory: How the Brain Stores You</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Memory is distributed reconstruction: the brain rebuilds the past, not replaying a perfect file.</p>
      <p class="subtitle">{updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key ideas</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card"><h3>Encoding depends on attention</h3><p>What we notice and rehearse is what gets consolidated.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Storage is networked</h3><p>Different regions handle facts, skills, and emotional associations.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Recall rewrites memory</h3><p>Each retrieval updates traces, blending old and new context.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Mental model</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <ul>
        <li>Experience is encoded across neural circuits.</li>
        <li>Sleep and repetition strengthen useful traces.</li>
        <li>Retrieval reconstructs and may modify the memory.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Why are eyewitness memories unreliable?</summary><p>Confidence can rise while accuracy drops after suggestion and repetition.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Can memory improve?</summary><p>Yes, through spacing, retrieval practice, and contextual cues.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Why forget at all?</summary><p>Forgetting reduces noise and preserves flexibility.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav">
      <a class="btn" href="/science">← Science index</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future">Explore Future →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>

</ArticleLayout>
